How We use your personal data and who We share it with\r\n        </strong>\r\n    </a>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    6.1 This section explains how We use the personal data listed above and who\r\n    We share it with.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    6.2 We use your personal data:\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (a)\r\n    <strong>\r\n        To manage your bookings with Us and to provide the services or\r\n        membership benefits that you request before, during and after your\r\n        cruise\r\n    </strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    We need to use your personal data to deliver Our services to you when you\r\n    book a cruise. For example, when you travel with Us We need your personal\r\n    data to send you a booking confirmation, to manage changes to your booking,\r\n    to check you in when you board Our ships and to keep track of you onboard,\r\n    to deliver your benefits for Our loyalty programs, to provide you with\r\n    further products and services onboard (for example when you book shore\r\n    excursions, tours or onboard entertainment and when you make purchases in\r\n    Our shops, restaurants, and casinos).\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (b) <strong>To help you contact Our customer support services</strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    When you get in touch with Our customer support services (whether through\r\n    the Digital Platforms or otherwise), We will process your personal\r\n    information so that you receive the best customer service possible.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (c) <strong>For your safety </strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    Your safety is important to Us, and We use y, [2018-08-26T19:03:35-0400] [ALL] 08-26 22:30:54.190 24683 24754 D OkHttp  : our details to safeguard it.\r\n    For example, We transfer a record of the personal data you provide during\r\n    the booking process onto your cruise ship for use if you require medical\r\n    assistance. Additionally, We check booking details against law enforcement\r\n    registers and Our internal records for the safety of all customers. We also\r\n    use closed-circuit television (\"CCTV\") cameras onboard Our ships and equip\r\n    Our security staff with body cameras for your safety. If circumstances\r\n    allow, We will notify you before We begin recording with a body camera.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (d)\r\n    <strong>\r\n        To make Our Digital Platforms easy to use and enhance your\r\n        cruise-planning experience\r\n    </strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    The personal data We collect when you use Our Digital Platforms helps Us to\r\n    make sure that Our Digital Platforms work well (for example, so that We\r\n    know it is you when you sign into your account). Were often improving Our\r\n    Digital Platforms and content therein to enhance your cruise-planning\r\n    experience, and data about how you use Our site helps Us to do that. We\r\n    also use this data to help Us understand interest in the different sections\r\n    of Our Digital Platforms and the products and services that We sell online.\r\n    We also use your data to make the cruise booking process more convenient.\r\n    For example, We can remember what you have searched for so you can pick up\r\n    where you left off. We also use your information to fix operational\r\n    problems with the Digital Platforms such as software bugs and to maintain\r\n    the safety and security of the Digital Platforms.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (e)\r\n    <strong>\r\n        To manage your relationship with Us as a consumer and to deliver\r\n        personalized service\r\n    </strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    When you sign up via Our Digital Platforms or make a booking, We create a\r\n    consumer profile of you in Our systems. This is your digital profile that\r\n    brings the personal data that We maintain and identifies you across the\r\n    Royal Caribbean Group. Your consumer profile lets Us deliver a personalized\r\n    experience when you search for cruises, book and travel with Us or contact\r\n    Us by phone or email. We also use your consumer profile to personalize the\r\n    marketing communications that We send you. We also sometimes use your\r\n    details to ask for feedback on Our services.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (f) <strong>To process payments and invoicing</strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    When you make a purchase through the Digital Platforms (whether in relation\r\n    to a cruise or certain products or services such as shore excursions), We\r\n    will process your payment details to process the transaction.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    <strong>(g) For marketing and promotional purposes</strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    We use your contact details for Our marketing and promotions, including to\r\n    send you information about the products and services that We and the Royal\r\n    Caribbean Group offer. We also use your personal data to personalize Our\r\n    marketing communications to make them more relevant for you and to measure\r\n    engagement with Our marketing campaigns. Additionally, We keep records to assist with any complaints you\r\n    may have or in the event of a legal claim. Our privacy\r\n    notice will not cover the information collected by travel partners and it\r\n    will not cover how travel partners use that information. For example, We use travel booking systems to provide flight\r\n    availability and cost details, and to book flights if required by you in\r\n    connection with your cruise.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (d) <strong>Our Business Partners</strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    We partner with companies, such as tour operators, to complement the\r\n    products and services that We provide to you. We only do this in compliance\r\n    with applicable law.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    <strong>\r\n        (e) Ports, customs and other government authorities, law enforcement\r\n        agencies, courts, and parties to litigation\r\n    </strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    We may need to share your personal data where required under the laws of\r\n    countries in which We operate. Direct marketing</strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    8.1 Marketing communications from Us - We may contact you for marketing\r\n    purposes, including to tell you more about Our services, share news or tell\r\n    you about promotions from time to time. You can opt out at any time using the same options\r\n    above.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    <a name=\"profiling\">\r\n        <strong>9. Profiling and personalized marketing</strong>\r\n    </a>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    9.1 Profiling overview: We think it is important for Us to understand the\r\n    types of vacations that Our consumers are interested in so that We can make\r\n    Our marketing relevant and targeted. To do this, We use your personal data\r\n    to build a profile for you that lets Us work out which of Our marketing\r\n    segments is the best fit for you.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    9.2 The personal data We use: From the personal data that We hold about\r\n    you, Our model may consider your age, gender, household or travel\r\n    composition, postcode, how you have interacted with Our websites and\r\n    marketing emails and your booking history (including your destinations, the\r\n    ships you have sailed on and your chosen accommodation). We do not always\r\n    use all of these data categories if We do not have the information about\r\n    you or it is not relevant for Our marketing activities.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    9.3 How We build your profile and what We learn from it:\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (a) <strong>Statistical analysis</strong> - We use the data above as inputs\r\n    for a proprietary statistical model, the output of which can tell Us about\r\n    your previous or likely f, [2018-08-26T19:03:35-0400] [ALL] 08-26 22:30:54.191 24683 24754 D OkHttp  : uture booking behavior, for example:\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (i) the value or likely value of the bookings you make with Us;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (ii) whether you tend to re-book within 12 months of your last cruise and\r\n    the destinations that you tend to book; and\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (iii) the extent to which you engage with Our marketing emails.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (b) <strong>Marketing segments </strong> We try to match every consumer\r\n    with one or more pre-defined segments that allow Us to broadly tailor Our\r\n    marketing messages for the right audience. We define Our segments using\r\n    anonymized demographic data based on broad characteristics and behaviors\r\n    such as age, household income, or location. You will share a segment with\r\n    other consumers, so this process is generally not highly individualized.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    9.4 <strong>Heres an example:</strong> Lets say you have just signed up\r\n    on Our websites (giving Us your contact details) and you have never booked\r\n    a cruise before. Over the next few days you search for cruises that are\r\n    generally popular with families (giving Us website interaction data). We\r\n    might use that data to add you to one of Our family segments so that you\r\n    get relevant emails from Us.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    9.5 <strong>What this means for you: </strong>Tailoring Our marketing\r\n    campaigns to your profile or segment means you should receive more relevant\r\n    communications from Us. Thats good for Us because We think you are more\r\n    likely to book a vacation that matches your requirements. We hope thats\r\n    good for you, too, because it helps you to find the vacations that you are\r\n    interested in. We might also send you special offers on your birthday.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    9.6\r\n    <strong>\r\n        Targeted advertising on third party social media platforms and\r\n        websites:\r\n    </strong>\r\n    We may share your personal data  including your name, email address,\r\n    address and date of birth  with third party social media platforms,\r\n    including Facebook, and websites for the purposes of allowing those\r\n    platforms to display targeted advertisements to you. Cookies and other tracking technologies</strong>\r\n    </a>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    10.1 We use cookie data and other technologies to collect information on\r\n    Our web pages for a variety of purposes, such as to improve the design and\r\n    content of Our website and to enable Us to provide a more personalized\r\n    experience when you browse the Internet. We also use cookies for\r\n    advertising and targeted tracking purposes, which aims to improve the\r\n    relevance of the advertisements you see. Acting on someone elses behalf </strong>\r\n    </a>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    12.1 If you give Us information about another person (or persons), such as\r\n    another guest, We will understand this to mean that they have appointed and\r\n    authorized you to act on their behalf. This includes providing consent (to\r\n    the extent this is required) to:\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (a) Us processing their personal data; and\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (b) you receiving any information protection notices on their behalf.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    We may ask you to provide evidence that you have been appointed and\r\n    authorized to act on behalf of the other person (or persons).\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    <strong>13. Multi-guest reservations and linking reservations</strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    13.1 If you make a multi-guest reservation, all of the guests who are part\r\n    of the reservation will be able to access the personal data of the other\r\n    guests on Our Digital Platforms.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    13.2 Our Digital Platforms will allow your reservation  as well as your\r\n    personal data therein - to be associated to another user's guest account\r\n    provided you have furnished certain credentials or unique identifiers to\r\n    them. We call this \"linking. If your reservation is linked by another user\r\n    of Our Digital Platforms, We will allow the user who has linked your\r\n    account to (1) complete online check-in for you and others in your\r\n    reservation, (2) view your boarding pass, and the boarding pass of others\r\n    in your reservation, (3) pay for an onboard or shore product or activity\r\n    for you or others in your reservation, using their own onboard expense\r\n    account or their own payment methods, and (4) view eDocs associated to your\r\n    reservation. However, they will not be able to modify or cancel your\r\n    reservation, view your folio or use a digital key to access your stateroom.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    <strong>14. Children</strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    14.1 Our Digital Platforms seek to promote Our cruise vacations for sale to\r\n    adults. The FCC is\r\n    non-transferable, non-refundable, and not redeemable for any other form of\r\n    compensation, credit, or cash. Arbitration is less formal than a lawsuit in\r\n        court. Arbitration uses a neutral arbitrator instead of a judge or\r\n        jury, may allow for more limited discovery than in court, and can be\r\n        subject to very limited review by courts. How We use your personal data and who We share it with\r\n        </strong>\r\n    </a>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    6.1 This section explains how We use the personal data listed above and who\r\n    We share it with.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    6.2 We use your personal data:\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (a)\r\n    <strong>\r\n        To manage your bookings with Us and to provide the services or\r\n        membership benefits that you request before, during and after your\r\n        cruise\r\n    </strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    We need to use your personal data to deliver Our services to you when you\r\n    book a cruise. For example, when you travel with Us We need your personal\r\n    data to send you a booking confirmation, to manage changes to your booking,\r\n    to check you in when you board Our ships and to keep track of you onboard,\r\n    to deliver your benefits for Our loyalty programs, to provide you with\r\n    further products and services onboard (for example when you book shore\r\n    excursions, tours or onboard entertainment and when you make purchases in\r\n    Our shops, restaurants, and casinos).\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (b) <strong>To help you contact Our customer support services</strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    When you get in touch with Our customer support services (whether through\r\n    the Digital Platforms or otherwise), We will process your personal\r\n    information so that you receive the best customer service possible.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (c) <strong>For your safety </strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    Your safety is important to Us, and We use y, [2018-08-26T19:04:03-0400] [ALL] 08-26 23:04:03.637 25006 25070 D OkHttp  : our details to safeguard it.\r\n    For example, We transfer a record of the personal data you provide during\r\n    the booking process onto your cruise ship for use if you require medical\r\n    assistance. Additionally, We check booking details against law enforcement\r\n    registers and Our internal records for the safety of all customers. We also\r\n    use closed-circuit television (\"CCTV\") cameras onboard Our ships and equip\r\n    Our security staff with body cameras for your safety. If circumstances\r\n    allow, We will notify you before We begin recording with a body camera.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (d)\r\n    <strong>\r\n        To make Our Digital Platforms easy to use and enhance your\r\n        cruise-planning experience\r\n    </strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    The personal data We collect when you use Our Digital Platforms helps Us to\r\n    make sure that Our Digital Platforms work well (for example, so that We\r\n    know it is you when you sign into your account). Were often improving Our\r\n    Digital Platforms and content therein to enhance your cruise-planning\r\n    experience, and data about how you use Our site helps Us to do that. We\r\n    also use this data to help Us understand interest in the different sections\r\n    of Our Digital Platforms and the products and services that We sell online.\r\n    We also use your data to make the cruise booking process more convenient.\r\n    For example, We can remember what you have searched for so you can pick up\r\n    where you left off. We also use your information to fix operational\r\n    problems with the Digital Platforms such as software bugs and to maintain\r\n    the safety and security of the Digital Platforms.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (e)\r\n    <strong>\r\n        To manage your relationship with Us as a consumer and to deliver\r\n        personalized service\r\n    </strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    When you sign up via Our Digital Platforms or make a booking, We create a\r\n    consumer profile of you in Our systems. This is your digital profile that\r\n    brings the personal data that We maintain and identifies you across the\r\n    Royal Caribbean Group. Your consumer profile lets Us deliver a personalized\r\n    experience when you search for cruises, book and travel with Us or contact\r\n    Us by phone or email. We also use your consumer profile to personalize the\r\n    marketing communications that We send you. We also sometimes use your\r\n    details to ask for feedback on Our services.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (f) <strong>To process payments and invoicing</strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    When you make a purchase through the Digital Platforms (whether in relation\r\n    to a cruise or certain products or services such as shore excursions), We\r\n    will process your payment details to process the transaction.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    <strong>(g) For marketing and promotional purposes</strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    We use your contact details for Our marketing and promotions, including to\r\n    send you information about the products and services that We and the Royal\r\n    Caribbean Group offer. We also use your personal data to personalize Our\r\n    marketing communications to make them more relevant for you and to measure\r\n    engagement with Our marketing campaigns. In such instances, We will not turn over records or other\r\n    information pertaining to you unless compelled to do so by a Court of\r\n    competent jurisdiction pursuant to the provisions of the SCA.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (i) <strong>For Our business operations</strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    We may use your personal data for business management activities, including\r\n    to assist with incident management and to enable Us to conduct reporting.\r\n    Reports help Us to monitor Our performance and the performance of Our\r\n    Suppliers. Additionally, We keep records to assist with any complaints you\r\n    may have or in the event of a legal claim. Our privacy\r\n    notice will not cover the information collected by travel partners and it\r\n    will not cover how travel partners use that information. We only do this in compliance\r\n    with applicable law.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    <strong>\r\n        (e) Ports, customs and other government authorities, law enforcement\r\n        agencies, courts, and parties to litigation\r\n    </strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    We may need to share your personal data where required under the laws of\r\n    countries in which We operate. Calling Our call centers</strong></a>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    7.1 In certain circumstances, We may re-route calls from Our call centers\r\n    which are based inside the EEA to call centers based outside of the EEA. Direct marketing</strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    8.1 Marketing communications from Us - We may contact you for marketing\r\n    purposes, including to tell you more about Our services, share news or tell\r\n    you about promotions from time to time. You are in control of the emails\r\n    and texts that you receive, and you can update your preferences or opt out\r\n    at any time via your Guest Account, following the links in Our emails or by\r\n    contacting Us using the details provided below. Even if you have opted out\r\n    of marketing messages, We will still need to contact you in relation to\r\n    your bookings with Us.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    8.2 Marketing communications from other members of the Royal Caribbean\r\n    Group Some of the services and activities provided onboard Our ships are\r\n    managed by other members of the Royal Caribbean Group. These members may\r\n    contact you about those services and activities  including information and\r\n    promotions relating to onboard casinos  if you have opted-in to receive\r\n    marketing communications from the Royal Caribbean Group or where permitted\r\n    by applicable law. You can opt out at any time using the same options\r\n    above.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    <a name=\"profiling\">\r\n        <strong>9. Profiling and personalized marketing</strong>\r\n    </a>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    9.1 Profiling overview: We think it is important for Us to understand the\r\n    types of vacations that Our consumers are interested in so that We can make\r\n    Our marketing relevant and targeted. To do this, We use your personal data\r\n    to build a profile for you that lets Us work out which of Our marketing\r\n    segments is the best fit for you.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    9.2 The personal data We use: From the personal data that We hold about\r\n    you, Our model may consider your age, gender, household or travel\r\n    composition, postcode, how you have interacted with Our websites and\r\n    marketing emails and your booking history (including your destinations, the\r\n    ships you have sailed on and your chosen accommodation). We do not always\r\n    use all of these data categories if We do not have the information about\r\n    you or it is not relevant for Our marketing activities.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    9.3 How We build your profile and what We learn from it:\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (a) <strong>Statistical analysis</strong> - We use the data above as inputs\r\n    for a proprietary statistical model, the output of which can tell Us about\r\n    your previous or likely f, [2018-08-26T19:04:03-0400] [ALL] 08-26 23:04:03.671 25006 25070 D OkHttp  : uture booking behavior, for example:\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (i) the value or likely value of the bookings you make with Us;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (ii) whether you tend to re-book within 12 months of your last cruise and\r\n    the destinations that you tend to book; and\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (iii) the extent to which you engage with Our marketing emails.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (b) <strong>Marketing segments </strong> We try to match every consumer\r\n    with one or more pre-defined segments that allow Us to broadly tailor Our\r\n    marketing messages for the right audience. We define Our segments using\r\n    anonymized demographic data based on broad characteristics and behaviors\r\n    such as age, household income, or location. You will share a segment with\r\n    other consumers, so this process is generally not highly individualized.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    9.4 <strong>Heres an example:</strong> Lets say you have just signed up\r\n    on Our websites (giving Us your contact details) and you have never booked\r\n    a cruise before. Over the next few days you search for cruises that are\r\n    generally popular with families (giving Us website interaction data). We\r\n    might use that data to add you to one of Our family segments so that you\r\n    get relevant emails from Us.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    9.5 <strong>What this means for you: </strong>Tailoring Our marketing\r\n    campaigns to your profile or segment means you should receive more relevant\r\n    communications from Us. Thats good for Us because We think you are more\r\n    likely to book a vacation that matches your requirements. We hope thats\r\n    good for you, too, because it helps you to find the vacations that you are\r\n    interested in. How We use your personal data and who We share it with\r\n        </strong>\r\n    </a>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    6.1 This section explains how We use the personal data listed above and who\r\n    We share it with.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    6.2 We use your personal data:\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (a)\r\n    <strong>\r\n        To manage your bookings with Us and to provide the services or\r\n        membership benefits that you request before, during and after your\r\n        cruise\r\n    </strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    We need to use your personal data to deliver Our services to you when you\r\n    book a cruise. For example, when you travel with Us We need your personal\r\n    data to send you a booking confirmation, to manage changes to your booking,\r\n    to check you in when you board Our ships and to keep track of you onboard,\r\n    to deliver your benefits for Our loyalty programs, to provide you with\r\n    further products and services onboard (for example when you book shore\r\n    excursions, tours or onboard entertainment and when you make purchases in\r\n    Our shops, restaurants, and casinos).\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (b) <strong>To help you contact Our customer support services</strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    When you get in touch with Our customer support services (whether through\r\n    the Digital Platforms or otherwise), We will process your personal\r\n    information so that you receive the best customer service possible.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (c) <strong>For your safety </strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    Your safety is important to Us, and We use y, [2018-08-26T19:04:07-0400] [ALL] 08-26 23:04:07.624 25006 25067 D OkHttp  : our details to safeguard it.\r\n    For example, We transfer a record of the personal data you provide during\r\n    the booking process onto your cruise ship for use if you require medical\r\n    assistance. Additionally, We check booking details against law enforcement\r\n    registers and Our internal records for the safety of all customers. We also\r\n    use closed-circuit television (\"CCTV\") cameras onboard Our ships and equip\r\n    Our security staff with body cameras for your safety. If circumstances\r\n    allow, We will notify you before We begin recording with a body camera.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (d)\r\n    <strong>\r\n        To make Our Digital Platforms easy to use and enhance your\r\n        cruise-planning experience\r\n    </strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    The personal data We collect when you use Our Digital Platforms helps Us to\r\n    make sure that Our Digital Platforms work well (for example, so that We\r\n    know it is you when you sign into your account). Were often improving Our\r\n    Digital Platforms and content therein to enhance your cruise-planning\r\n    experience, and data about how you use Our site helps Us to do that. We\r\n    also use this data to help Us understand interest in the different sections\r\n    of Our Digital Platforms and the products and services that We sell online.\r\n    We also use your data to make the cruise booking process more convenient.\r\n    For example, We can remember what you have searched for so you can pick up\r\n    where you left off. We also use your information to fix operational\r\n    problems with the Digital Platforms such as software bugs and to maintain\r\n    the safety and security of the Digital Platforms.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (e)\r\n    <strong>\r\n        To manage your relationship with Us as a consumer and to deliver\r\n        personalized service\r\n    </strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    When you sign up via Our Digital Platforms or make a booking, We create a\r\n    consumer profile of you in Our systems. This is your digital profile that\r\n    brings the personal data that We maintain and identifies you across the\r\n    Royal Caribbean Group. Your consumer profile lets Us deliver a personalized\r\n    experience when you search for cruises, book and travel with Us or contact\r\n    Us by phone or email. We also use your consumer profile to personalize the\r\n    marketing communications that We send you. We also sometimes use your\r\n    details to ask for feedback on Our services.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (f) <strong>To process payments and invoicing</strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    When you make a purchase through the Digital Platforms (whether in relation\r\n    to a cruise or certain products or services such as shore excursions), We\r\n    will process your payment details to process the transaction.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    <strong>(g) For marketing and promotional purposes</strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    We use your contact details for Our marketing and promotions, including to\r\n    send you information about the products and services that We and the Royal\r\n    Caribbean Group offer. We also use your personal data to personalize Our\r\n    marketing communications to make them more relevant for you and to measure\r\n    engagement with Our marketing campaigns. See\r\n    <a\r\n        href=\"https://www.celebritycruises.co.uk/terms-and-conditions/privacy-policy/\"\r\n    >\r\n        Direct Marketing\r\n    </a>\r\n    and\r\n    <a\r\n        href=\"https://www.celebritycruises.co.uk/terms-and-conditions/privacy-policy/\"\r\n    >\r\n        Profiling and personalized marketing\r\n    </a>\r\n    below for more information, including on how to update your preferences and\r\n    opt out.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    We use personal data for additional marketing and promotional activities\r\n    relating to onboard casinos by tracking guest play to: (i) deliver related\r\n    loyalty program benefits; (ii) rank players; (iii) send casino-re, [2018-08-26T19:04:07-0400] [ALL] 08-26 23:04:07.624 25006 25067 D OkHttp  : lated\r\n    direct marketing messages; (iv) grant credit to groups playing casinos; and\r\n    (v) better understand how players use the onboard casinos.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (h) <strong>For compliance with Our legal obligations</strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    We are sometimes subject to certain legal requirements to collect, retain,\r\n    and disclose your personal data, for example for customs agencies or port\r\n    authorities to allow Our ships to dock, or where We need to cooperate with\r\n    law enforcement agencies, including in relation to criminal investigations.\r\n    Pursuant to the United States Stored Communications Act (the SCA), We may\r\n    be considered a provider of electronic communication services for certain\r\n    services We offer through the Digital Platforms (because We provide users\r\n    of the Digital Platforms the ability to send or receive wire or electronic\r\n    communications). In such instances, We will not turn over records or other\r\n    information pertaining to you unless compelled to do so by a Court of\r\n    competent jurisdiction pursuant to the provisions of the SCA.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (i) <strong>For Our business operations</strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    We may use your personal data for business management activities, including\r\n    to assist with incident management and to enable Us to conduct reporting.\r\n    Reports help Us to monitor Our performance and the performance of Our\r\n    Suppliers. Additionally, We keep records to assist with any complaints you\r\n    may have or in the event of a legal claim. We also process your feedback to\r\n    improve Our products and services.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    6.3 We may share your personal data with the following recipients for the\r\n    purposes listed above:\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (a) <strong>Other members of the Royal Caribbean Group </strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    We are a global business and We may need to share your personal data with\r\n    other members of the Royal Caribbean Group for the purposes above.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (b) <strong>Travel partner and Our international partners</strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    When you book through a travel partner or one of Our local partners, We may\r\n    need to send details of your booking to that partner. Travel partners may\r\n    make decisions themselves about how and why to process your information, or\r\n    they may or may not process your information on Our behalf. Our privacy\r\n    notice will not cover the information collected by travel partners and it\r\n    will not cover how travel partners use that information. We recommend that\r\n    you check your travel partners own privacy policy for details as to how\r\n    they may process your personal data.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (c) <strong>Our Suppliers </strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    We use products and services from Our Suppliers in the operation of Our\r\n    business. For example, We use travel booking systems to provide flight\r\n    availability and cost details, and to book flights if required by you in\r\n    connection with your cruise.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (d) <strong>Our Business Partners</strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    We partner with companies, such as tour operators, to complement the\r\n    products and services that We provide to you. We only do this in compliance\r\n    with applicable law.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    <strong>\r\n        (e) Ports, customs and other government authorities, law enforcement\r\n        agencies, courts, and parties to litigation\r\n    </strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    We may need to share your personal data where required under the laws of\r\n    countries in which We operate. Local ports and customs authorities require\r\n    passenger details to process Our ships in the ports at which they call. Law\r\n    enforcement agencies may also require access to personal data, including in\r\n    connection with criminal investigations, or We may be ordered to disclose\r\n    pe, [2018-08-26T19:04:07-0400] [ALL] 08-26 23:04:07.624 25006 25067 D OkHttp  : rsonal data by a court or in connection with legal proceedings.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (f) <strong>Other third parties</strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    We may share your personal data with other third parties at your request.\r\n    Our Digital Platforms may provide links to websites or other digital tools\r\n    that We believe may be useful to you in addition to advertisements placed\r\n    by third parties. These may lead you to websites or digital tools operated\r\n    by third parties operating under their own privacy policies. We encourage\r\n    you to review those privacy policies, as We have no control over those\r\n    third parties nor the information you may submit to those third parties.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    <a name=\"directmarketing\"><strong>7. Calling Our call centers</strong></a>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    7.1 In certain circumstances, We may re-route calls from Our call centers\r\n    which are based inside the EEA to call centers based outside of the EEA. In\r\n    these circumstances, We will let you know at the beginning of your call\r\n    that your call is being rerouted. Direct marketing</strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    8.1 Marketing communications from Us - We may contact you for marketing\r\n    purposes, including to tell you more about Our services, share news or tell\r\n    you about promotions from time to time. You are in control of the emails\r\n    and texts that you receive, and you can update your preferences or opt out\r\n    at any time via your Guest Account, following the links in Our emails or by\r\n    contacting Us using the details provided below. Even if you have opted out\r\n    of marketing messages, We will still need to contact you in relation to\r\n    your bookings with Us.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    8.2 Marketing communications from other members of the Royal Caribbean\r\n    Group Some of the services and activities provided onboard Our ships are\r\n    managed by other members of the Royal Caribbean Group. These members may\r\n    contact you about those services and activities  including information and\r\n    promotions relating to onboard casinos  if you have opted-in to receive\r\n    marketing communications from the Royal Caribbean Group or where permitted\r\n    by applicable law. You can opt out at any time using the same options\r\n    above.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    <a name=\"profiling\">\r\n        <strong>9. Profiling and personalized marketing</strong>\r\n    </a>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    9.1 Profiling overview: We think it is important for Us to understand the\r\n    types of vacations that Our consumers are interested in so that We can make\r\n    Our marketing relevant and targeted. To do this, We use your personal data\r\n    to build a profile for you that lets Us work out which of Our marketing\r\n    segments is the best fit for you.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    9.2 The personal data We use: From the personal data that We hold about\r\n    you, Our model may consider your age, gender, household or travel\r\n    composition, postcode, how you have interacted with Our websites and\r\n    marketing emails and your booking history (including your destinations, the\r\n    ships you have sailed on and your chosen accommodation). We do not always\r\n    use all of these data categories if We do not have the information about\r\n    you or it is not relevant for Our marketing activities.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    9.3 How We build your profile and what We learn from it:\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (a) <strong>Statistical analysis</strong> - We use the data above as inputs\r\n    for a proprietary statistical model, the output of which can tell Us about\r\n    your previous or likely f, [2018-08-26T19:04:07-0400] [ALL] 08-26 23:04:07.624 25006 25067 D OkHttp  : uture booking behavior, for example:\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (i) the value or likely value of the bookings you make with Us;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (ii) whether you tend to re-book within 12 months of your last cruise and\r\n    the destinations that you tend to book; and\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (iii) the extent to which you engage with Our marketing emails.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (b) <strong>Marketing segments </strong> We try to match every consumer\r\n    with one or more pre-defined segments that allow Us to broadly tailor Our\r\n    marketing messages for the right audience. We define Our segments using\r\n    anonymized demographic data based on broad characteristics and behaviors\r\n    such as age, household income, or location. You will share a segment with\r\n    other consumers, so this process is generally not highly individualized.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    9.4 <strong>Heres an example:</strong> Lets say you have just signed up\r\n    on Our websites (giving Us your contact details) and you have never booked\r\n    a cruise before. Over the next few days you search for cruises that are\r\n    generally popular with families (giving Us website interaction data). We\r\n    might use that data to add you to one of Our family segments so that you\r\n    get relevant emails from Us.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    9.5 <strong>What this means for you: </strong>Tailoring Our marketing\r\n    campaigns to your profile or segment means you should receive more relevant\r\n    communications from Us. Thats good for Us because We think you are more\r\n    likely to book a vacation that matches your requirements. We hope thats\r\n    good for you, too, because it helps you to find the vacations that you are\r\n    interested in. We might also send you special offers on your birthday.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    9.6\r\n    <strong>\r\n        Targeted advertising on third party social media platforms and\r\n        websites:\r\n    </strong>\r\n    We may share your personal data  including your name, email address,\r\n    address and date of birth  with third party social media platforms,\r\n    including Facebook, and websites for the purposes of allowing those\r\n    platforms to display targeted advertisements to you. You can ask Us not to\r\n    share your personal data with platforms, but you will need to contact the\r\n    platform with any requests in relation to how the platform uses your\r\n    personal data because We do not control that.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    9.7 <strong>You can opt out: </strong>You are in control of your personal\r\n    data. You can update your marketing preferences or opt out of personalized\r\n    marketing at any time using your Guest Account or, where you do not have a\r\n    Guest Account, by either clicking a link in an email marketing\r\n    communication, replying STOP to an SMS text message or by calling the\r\n    sender of any marketing communication.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    <a name=\"cookies\">\r\n        <strong>10. Cookies and other tracking technologies</strong>\r\n    </a>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    10.1 We use cookie data and other technologies to collect information on\r\n    Our web pages for a variety of purposes, such as to improve the design and\r\n    content of Our website and to enable Us to provide a more personalized\r\n    experience when you browse the Internet. We also use cookies for\r\n    advertising and targeted tracking purposes, which aims to improve the\r\n    relevance of the advertisements you see. The FCC is applicable only towards\r\n    the purchase of a Royal Caribbean International cruise and expires\r\n    12-months after the issue date (the \"Expiration Date\"). Any amount\r\n    remaining after the Expiration Date will be void and forfeited. The FCC is\r\n    non-transferable, non-refundable, and not redeemable for any other form of\r\n    compensation, credit, or cash. How We use your personal data and who We share it with\r\n        </strong>\r\n    </a>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    6.1 This section explains how We use the personal data listed above and who\r\n    We share it with.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    6.2 We use your personal data:\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (a)\r\n    <strong>\r\n        To manage your bookings with Us and to provide the services or\r\n        membership benefits that you request before, during and after your\r\n        cruise\r\n    </strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    We need to use your personal data to deliver Our services to you when you\r\n    book a cruise. For example, when you travel with Us We need your personal\r\n    data to send you a booking confirmation, to manage changes to your booking,\r\n    to check you in when you board Our ships and to keep track of you onboard,\r\n    to deliver your benefits for Our loyalty programs, to provide you with\r\n    further products and services onboard (for example when you book shore\r\n    excursions, tours or onboard entertainment and when you make purchases in\r\n    Our shops, restaurants, and casinos).\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (b) <strong>To help you contact Our customer support services</strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    When you get in touch with Our customer support services (whether through\r\n    the Digital Platforms or otherwise), We will process your personal\r\n    information so that you receive the best customer service possible.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (c) <strong>For your safety </strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    Your safety is important to Us, and We use your details to safeguard it.\r\n    For example, We transfer a record of the personal data you provide during\r\n    the booking process onto your cruise ship for use if you require medical\r\n    assistance. Additionally, We check booking details against law enforcement\r\n    registers and Our internal records for the safety of all customers. We also\r\n    use closed-circuit television (\"CCTV\") cameras onboard, [2018-08-26T19:04:08-0400] [ALL] 08-26 23:04:08.546 25006 25087 D RealmDataSource: RShip Insertion time: 2 ms, [2018-08-26T19:04:08-0400] [ALL] 08-26 23:04:08.551 25006 25060 D OkHttp  :  Our ships and equip\r\n    Our security staff with body cameras for your safety. Were often improving Our\r\n    Digital Platforms and content therein to enhance your cruise-planning\r\n    experience, and data about how you use Our site helps Us to do that. We\r\n    also use this data to help Us understand interest in the different sections\r\n    of Our Digital Platforms and the products and services that We sell online.\r\n    We also use your data to make the cruise booking process more convenient.\r\n    For example, We can remember what you have searched for so you can pick up\r\n    where you left off. Additionally, We keep records to assist with any complaints you\r\n    may have or in the event of a legal claim. We only do this in compliance\r\n    with applicable law.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    <strong>\r\n        (e) Ports, customs and other government authorities, law enforcement\r\n        agencies, courts, and parties to litigation\r\n    </strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    We may need to share your personal data where required under the laws of\r\n    countries in which We operate. You can opt out at any time using the same options\r\n    above.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    <a name=\"profiling\">\r\n        <strong>9. Profiling and personalized marketing</strong>\r\n    </a>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    9.1 Profiling overview: We think it is important for Us to understand the\r\n    types of vacations that Our consumers are interested in so that We can make\r\n    Our marketing relevant and targeted. To do this, We use your personal data\r\n    to build a profile for you that lets Us work out which of Our marketing\r\n    segments is the best fit for you.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    9.2 The personal data We use: From the personal data that We hold about\r\n    you, Our model may consider your age, gender, household or travel\r\n    composition, postcode, how you have interacted with Our websites and\r\n    marketing emails and your booking history (including your destinations, the\r\n    ships you have sailed on and your chosen accommodation). We do not always\r\n    use all of these data categories if We do not have the information about\r\n    you or it is not relevant for Our marketing activities.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    9.3 How We build your profile and what We learn from it:\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (a) <strong>Statistical analysis</strong> - We use the data above as inputs\r\n    for a proprietary statistical model, the output of which can tell Us about\r\n    your previous or likely future booking behavior, for example:\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (i) the value or likely value of the bookings you make with Us;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (ii) whether you tend to re-book within 12 months of your last cruise and\r\n    the destinations that you tend to book; and\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (iii) the extent to which you engage with Our marketing emails.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    (b) <strong>Marketing segments </strong>, [2018-08-26T19:04:08-0400] [ALL] 08-26 23:04:08.554 25006 25060 D OkHttp  :  We try to match every consumer\r\n    with one or more pre-defined segments that allow Us to broadly tailor Our\r\n    marketing messages for the right audience. We define Our segments using\r\n    anonymized demographic data based on broad characteristics and behaviors\r\n    such as age, household income, or location. You will share a segment with\r\n    other consumers, so this process is generally not highly individualized.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    9.4 <strong>Heres an example:</strong> Lets say you have just signed up\r\n    on Our websites (giving Us your contact details) and you have never booked\r\n    a cruise before.
